Here's the TUnit lifecycle at each scope:

---

### 1. Before/after every individual test in a class

```csharp
public class OrderTests
{
    [Before(Test)]
    public async Task ResetDatabase(TestContext context)
    {
        await InMemoryDb.ResetAsync();
    }

    [After(Test)]
    public async Task Cleanup(TestContext context)
    {
        // optional per-test teardown
    }

    [Test]
    public async Task Order_WithNoItems_Throws() { /* ... */ }
}
```

---

### 2. Once before the first / after the last test in a class

```csharp
public class OrderTests
{
    [Before(Class)]
    public static async Task OpenFixture(ClassHookContext context)
    {
        // runs once before any test in this class
    }

    [After(Class)]
    public static async Task DisposeFixture(ClassHookContext context)
    {
        // runs once after all tests in this class complete
    }

    [Test]
    public async Task PlaceOrder_Succeeds() { /* ... */ }
}
```

> `[Before(Class)]` / `[After(Class)]` methods must be **static**.

---

### 3. Once before/after all tests in the assembly

```csharp
public class WireMockSetup
{
    [Before(Assembly)]
    public static async Task StartWireMock(AssemblyHookContext context)
    {
        // start in-process WireMock server
    }

    [After(Assembly)]
    public static async Task StopWireMock(AssemblyHookContext context)
    {
        // tear down WireMock
    }
}
```

---

### 4. Once at the very start/end of the entire test session

```csharp
public class GlobalDatabaseMigration
{
    [Before(TestSession)]
    public static async Task ApplyMigrations(TestSessionContext context)
    {
        await EfCoreMigrator.MigrateAsync();
    }

    [After(TestSession)]
    public static async Task TearDownDatabase(TestSessionContext context)
    {
        await EfCoreMigrator.DropAsync();
    }
}
```

---

### Quick-reference table

| Scope | Before | After | Method must be |
|-------|--------|-------|----------------|
| Each test | `[Before(Test)]` | `[After(Test)]` | Instance |
| Class (once) | `[Before(Class)]` | `[After(Class)]` | `static` |
| Assembly (once) | `[Before(Assembly)]` | `[After(Assembly)]` | `static` |
| Session (once) | `[Before(TestSession)]` | `[After(TestSession)]` | `static` |

**Bonus:** Use `[BeforeEvery(Test)]` / `[AfterEvery(Test)]` (static, on any class) to hook *every* test globally — handy for cross-cutting concerns like logging. All hooks can optionally accept a `CancellationToken` parameter as well.
